200.1 - Medir e Resolver problemas de uso de recursos - iostat, vmstat e mpstat

iostat - Reports CPU, disk I/O, and NFS statistcs
vmstat - Reports virtual memory statistics 
mpstat - Reports processors statistics 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

IOSTAT - Reports CPU, disl I/O, and NFS statistics 

Campos

avg-cpu: Carga m√©dia de processamento

%user: 

User level

%nice: 

Nice priority.

%system: 

System level (Kernel).

%iowait: 

CPUs idle 

%steal: Idle CPUs virtual request 


DEVICE 

tps - Transfers per second

KB_read/s - Block read per second 

KB_wrtn/s - Block writtten per second 

KB_read - Total read per second 

KB_wrtn - Total written per second 


Show Statistics CPUs 

iostat -c 

Show Statistics Device 

iostat -d 

Show Statistics partition 

iostat -p /dev/sda1 

Show Version

iostat -V 

Show Statistics LVM 

iostat -N

Show Extend Statistics

iostat -x 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

VMSTAT - Report Virtual memory statistics 

r: Total number of processes waiting to run
b: Total number of busy processes

swapd: Used virtual memory 
free: Free virtual memory
buff: Memory used as buffers 
cache: Memory used as cache

si - swap in

so - swap out 

bi - block in

bo - block out
 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MPSTAT 

Report processors related statistics 

-u - Report utilization CPU


%irq

%soft

%steal

%guest

%gnice

%idle

